'''Ala kiyiz''' ({{lang-ky|ала кийиз}}, {{IPA-ky|ɑlɑ kijíz|}}) or '''tekemet''' ({{lang-kk|текемет}}, {{IPA-kk|ti̯ɘki̯ɘmi̯ɘ́t|}}) is a [[textile]] floor- or wall-covering made by pressing [[felt]] of various colours (often naturally different, and not dyed) together.  This is a traditional textile among the [[Kazakhs]] and [[Kyrgyz people|Kyrgyz]].<ref name="KyrgyzStyleProduction">{{cite web|url=http://www.kyrgyzstyle.kg/production/index.htm |title=Production |publisher=Kyrgyz Style |accessdate=2009-08-27 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091025073011/http://www.kyrgyzstyle.kg/production/index.htm |archivedate=2009-10-25 |df= }}</ref>

