'''Egal Shidad''' ({{lang-so|Cigaal Shiidaad, Egal Shidad}}; {{lang-ar|عيقال شيداد}}) is a [[folk hero]] that was known as the brave coward.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=S9vfAAAAMAAJ|title=Sheekooyinkii cigaal shidaad: The stories of egal shidad (the wise coward man)|first=Mohammed Sh|last=Hassan|date=1 January 2002|publisher=Scansom|accessdate=14 July 2016|via=Google Books}}</ref> 

From [[Somalia]], Egal Shidad was known for his dislike of wild animals and his inability to take risks.<ref name=one>{{cite web|url=http://scansom.com/product_info.php?products_id=98|title=The Travels of Igal Shidad (Bi-lingual), Scansom Publisher|publisher=|accessdate=14 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.authorsden.com/visit/viewshortstory.asp?id=25394 |title=Egal Shidad |publisher= |accessdate=14 July 2016 }}{{dead link|date=December 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
Like many [[Somali people]], Shidad was a nomadic herder of camel and sheep. He traveled the land with his herd in search of water and [[pasture]].<ref name=one/> Though he was a coward, Shidad was also wise. This resulted into many miscellaneous adventures.<ref name=one/>

Because of his stories Shidad has come to be known as a folk hero among the Somalis.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sahanjournal.com/rachel-pieh-jones-5-things-cigaal-shidaad-taught/#.V4fL-TVnjB4|title=5 things a foreigner learned from Cigaal Shidaad|date=18 April 2015|publisher=|accessdate=14 July 2016}}</ref>

